ew morale.\n- **Candidate\u202fC** excels in rapid, calm decision\u2011making and technical understanding, yet communication deficits and limited professional development raise crew\u2011cooperation concerns.\n- **Candidate\u202fD** shows superior problem\u2011solving, concentration, and responsibility, but a hot temper and \u201cknow\u2011it\u2011all\u201d attitude may undermine long\u2011duration crew dynamics.\n- **Candidate\u202fA** provides excellent hazard anticipation, systems thinking, spatial vision, and leadership, but attitude issues and the absence of any stress\u2011tolerance evidence leave a critical safety gap.\n**Remaining uncertainties**\n- How severe are Candidate\u202fB\u2019s memory weaknesses in real navigation tasks?\n- Will Candidate\u202fB\u2019s nasty remarks actually erode crew cohesion under fatigue?\n- Can Candidate\u202fA\u2019s unknown stress response be trusted for extended high\u2011pressure operations?\n- To what extent can Candidate\u202fC\u2019s communication difficulties be compensated through crew\u2011resource training?\n- How frequently does Candidate\u202fD\u2019s hot temper manifest during prolonged stress, and what impact would it have on safety?\n**What would change my vote**\n- Concrete performance data (e.g., simulator or flight\u2011deck assessments) showing that Candidate\u202fB\u2019s numeric memory is sufficient and that his interpersonal behavior does not impair crew performance would solidify my support for B.\n- Conversely, strong, observable evidence that any other candidate (A, C, or D) demonstrates reliable stress tolerance, superior teamwork/communication, and no critical weaknesses would shift my preference to that candidate.\n- A clear overall performance advantage in a realistic long\u2011distance flight scenario that outweighs the current trade\u2011offs would also change my stance.\n**Confidence:**\u202fModerate (\u224855\u202f%); I remain open to revising my preference as new, concrete performance evidence becomes available.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}", "thoughts": "We need to produce public message and metadata as agent_2. Our current preferred candidate is Candidate B (as per our last turn). We need to summarize key evidence, evidence from others, major alternatives, main tradeoff, remaining uncertainty, what would change vote, confidence. Ensure we only use known attributes. Provide concise but thorough. Then metadata with vote \"Candidate B\". Let's craft.\n\nWe must not include extra text beyond the two sections. Ensure format exactly:\n\nPUBLIC_MESSAGE:\n<content>\n\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}\n\nProceed."}
